South Africa‘s Truworths International expects full-year profit to fall by as much 3%, the fashion retailer said on Friday, as retail sales declined. Diluted headline earnings per share (HEPS) for the 52-week period ended 1 July 2018 are expected to decrease by as much as 3% to between 601 cents and 615 cents per share compared with 621 cents from the comparable 52-week period the year before. HEPS is the main profit measure used in South African that strips out certain once-off items. Read: SA’s retail malaise rages on Group retail sales decreased by 2.7% from R18.5 billion ($1 billion) to R18.0 billion. Truworths results are expected to be released on 16 August.